      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To fix a low inventory turnover ratio caused by dead stock, you need to actively clear those piles of seasonal items rather than just accepting them. You can try aggressive discounting, bundling slow-moving pieces with fast sellers, or even donating the excess to local charities to free up your backroom space. Additionally, consider revising your purchasing strategy to be more conservative with next season's orders based on actual sales data from the current season. Implementing a strict \"sell or ship out\" policy for items older than a certain date can also force movement and prevent further accumulation of stagnant inventory.",
